[Crofsblogs comments: "I have no idea what fumigating and spraying are supposed to achieve against Ebola [virus disease], though the activities might reduce some vectorborne diseases like malaria. Otherwise, it's just public health theatre. More disturbing is the continuing gulf between government and people. The politicians can "call on" local communities to cooperate against the outbreak, but those communities seem reluctant to cooperate." http://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2014/07/liberia-the-politics-of-fighting-ebola.html. - Mod.JW]

